{
  "abstract" : [
    {
      "text" : "Build fully self-contained Swift executables and deploy them",
      "type" : "text"
    },
    {
      "text" : " ",
      "type" : "text"
    },
    {
      "text" : "to minimal containers or directly to Linux machines.",
      "type" : "text"
    }
  ],
  "hierarchy" : {
    "paths" : [
      [
        "doc:\/\/ServerGuides\/documentation\/ServerGuides"
      ]
    ]
  },
  "identifier" : {
    "interfaceLanguage" : "swift",
    "url" : "doc:\/\/ServerGuides\/documentation\/ServerGuides\/deploying-static-binaries"
  },
  "kind" : "article",
  "metadata" : {
    "modules" : [
      {
        "name" : "Server Guides"
      }
    ],
    "role" : "article",
    "roleHeading" : "Article",
    "title" : "Deploying Swift services as static binaries"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The Static Linux SDK produces Swift executables with no external dependencies —",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "not even the C library.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "This lets you run the binary on any Linux machine regardless of distribution,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "which opens deployment options that aren’t possible with dynamically linked builds.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "You can copy the binary into a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "scratch",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " or distroless container image that contains nothing but your executable.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Or skip containers entirely and copy the binary to a virtual machine.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Either way, the result is the smallest possible deployment artifact with the smallest possible attack surface.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "This article walks you through installing the SDK, building a static binary, and deploying it.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Install-the-Static-Linux-SDK",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Install the Static Linux SDK",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The Static Linux SDK requires an open source Swift toolchain.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "The toolchain bundled with Xcode doesn’t support SDK-based cross-compilation.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Use ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "swiftly",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " to install an open source Swift toolchain, then install the Static Linux SDK for that toolchain.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Go to ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/www.swift.org\/install\/",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " for the links and commands to install both.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Install the SDK with ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "swift sdk install",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ", providing the URL for your Swift version.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "The command follows this form:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "swift sdk install <url> --checksum <checksum>"
          ],
          "syntax" : "bash",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "After installation, verify the SDK is available:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "swift sdk list"
          ],
          "syntax" : "bash",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The output includes SDK names like ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "x86_64-swift-linux-musl",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "and ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "aarch64-swift-linux-musl",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " that you use in build commands.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Build-a-static-binary",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Build a static binary",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Build your service with the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "--swift-sdk",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " flag,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "specifying the target architecture:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "swift build -c release --swift-sdk aarch64-swift-linux-musl"
          ],
          "syntax" : "bash",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "For x86_64 targets, use the corresponding SDK name:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "swift build -c release --swift-sdk x86_64-swift-linux-musl"
          ],
          "syntax" : "bash",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "This produces a statically linked ELF binary in ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : ".build\/release\/",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "that you can copy to any Linux system and run directly.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "The SDK uses ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/musl.libc.org",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " instead of Glibc",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "and statically links everything the executable needs —",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "including the Swift standard library, Foundation, and system libraries",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "like libcurl and libxml2.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "Because Musl replaces Glibc,",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : "some packages that import C libraries need changes —",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : "for example, changing import lines from ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "code" : "Glibc",
                  "type" : "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " to ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "code" : "Musl",
                  "type" : "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text" : ".",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : "The Swift standard library and Foundation handle this automatically.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Note",
          "style" : "note",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Deploy-to-a-distroless-container-image",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Deploy to a distroless container image",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "A distroless container image contains no operating system utilities —",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "no package manager, no shell, nothing but what you put in it.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "This eliminates an entire class of potential vulnerabilities",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "because there are no extra programs an attacker could exploit.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Because the Static Linux SDK cross-compiles from your development machine,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "you don’t need a multi-stage Dockerfile with a Swift SDK builder image.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Build the binary locally, then use a minimal ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Dockerfile",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "that copies the pre-built executable into a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "scratch",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " image —",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "a completely empty base image:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "swift build -c release --swift-sdk aarch64-swift-linux-musl"
          ],
          "syntax" : "bash",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "FROM scratch",
            "COPY .build\/release\/<executable-name> \/",
            "",
            "EXPOSE 8080",
            "ENTRYPOINT [\"\/<executable-name>\"]"
          ],
          "syntax" : "Dockerfile",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The final image contains a single file: your executable.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "If your service makes outbound TLS connections,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "the image also needs CA certificates.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Copy them from any Linux image at build time:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "FROM ubuntu:noble AS certs",
            "RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends ca-certificates",
            "",
            "FROM scratch",
            "COPY --from=certs \/etc\/ssl\/certs\/ca-certificates.crt \/etc\/ssl\/certs\/",
            "COPY .build\/release\/<executable-name> \/",
            "",
            "EXPOSE 8080",
            "ENTRYPOINT [\"\/<executable-name>\"]"
          ],
          "syntax" : "Dockerfile",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Build the container image:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "container build -t <my-app>:latest ."
          ],
          "syntax" : "bash",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "A ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "code" : "scratch",
                  "type" : "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text" : "-based image doesn’t include a shell,",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : "so you can’t use ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "code" : "container run --rm -it <my-app> \/bin\/sh",
                  "type" : "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " to debug.",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : "If you need a shell for troubleshooting,",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : "use a slim base image during development and switch to ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "code" : "scratch",
                  "type" : "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " for production.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Note",
          "style" : "note",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Build-and-publish-with-Swift-Container-Plugin",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Build and publish with Swift Container Plugin",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-container-plugin",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "combines building, packaging, and pushing to a registry into a single command.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "It builds your service with the Static Linux SDK,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "packages the executable into a container image,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "and publishes the image to a container registry — all without a Dockerfile.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Add the plugin to your ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "Package.swift",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : ":",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "dependencies: [",
            "    .package(url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/apple\/swift-container-plugin\", from: \"0.1.0\"),",
            "],"
          ],
          "syntax" : "swift",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Then build and publish:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "swift package --swift-sdk aarch64-swift-linux-musl \\",
            "    build-container-image --repository registry.example.com\/my-app"
          ],
          "syntax" : "bash",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The plugin produces a minimal image equivalent to one from a ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "scratch",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : "-based Dockerfile",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "and pushes it to the specified registry.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "Run the published image with any container runtime:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "container run -p 8080:8080 registry.example.com\/my-app"
          ],
          "syntax" : "bash",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "The container plugin is especially useful in CI pipelines",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : "where you want a single, repeatable command",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : "that produces a ready-to-deploy image.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name" : "Tip",
          "style" : "tip",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Deploy-directly-to-a-Linux-machine",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Deploy directly to a Linux machine",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "A static binary runs on any Linux machine, so you can copy it directly to a virtual machine or bare-metal server:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "scp .build\/release\/<executable-name> user@server:\/usr\/local\/bin\/"
          ],
          "syntax" : "bash",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "On the server, run the executable directly:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "ssh user@server \/usr\/local\/bin\/<executable-name>"
          ],
          "syntax" : "bash",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Use your preferred configuration management tool, such as Ansible, Chef, Puppet, or shell scripts,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "to automate deployment across multiple hosts.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
  ],
